    <fr:title text="Matrices as tables"><fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">Matrices</fr:link> as tables</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Notation</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-<fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link></html:span> can be depicted in tables or grids with rows in the first dimension and columns in the second dimension. For example, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (3,2\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be the <fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link> over the booleans defined by the following equation:</fr:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 M_{i,j} =
 \begin {cases}
  \mathsf {true} &\text {if } \mathsf {parity}{\mathopen {}\left (i\right )\mathclose {}} = \mathsf {parity}{\mathopen {}\left (j\right )\mathclose {}}
  \\
  \mathsf {false} &\text {otherwise}
 \end {cases}
]]></fr:tex>
    <fr:p>Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is depicted by the following table with three rows and two columns:</fr:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 M =
 \begin {bmatrix}
  \mathsf {true} & \mathsf {false}\\
  \mathsf {false} & \mathsf {true}\\
  \mathsf {true} & \mathsf {false}
 \end {bmatrix}
]]></fr:tex>
  </fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:backmatter>
